        <h1>About Us</h1>
        <p>Dr Kristen Boyce, Kris, has been treating patients since 1994. He is a certified diplomat with the American Board of Foot and Ankle Surgery and a Fellow of the American College of Foot and Ankle Surgeons. He attended Western State College in Gunnison and having been a ski racer for 11 years desired a career in Sports Medicine. He could relate to the importance of proper foot function as well as performing with potential foot pain and after receiving his degree in Biology chose to pursue podiatry. He graduated from California College of Podiatric Medicine in San Francisco, followed by surgical residency programs in San Francisco and Travis Air Force Base. He was in practice in Fort Collins for 6 years before moving back to the mountains to start Steamboat Podiatry Clinic in 2001.</p>

        <img src="images/line.gif" alt="" width="1094" height="1" border="0" style="padding-top:35px; padding-bottom:10px;">
        <div id="service">
            <h1>Podiatry Services</h1>
            <p>To diagnose, prescribe, and treat foot and ankle conditions. Dr Boyce has treated patients ranging in age from 2 days old to 102 years; the sedentary individual to the professional athlete. His philosophy is to address the chief complaint and offer treatment that allows pain-free activity.</p>

            <h2>Surgical procedures include:</h2>
            <p>Bunion surgery, hammertoe correction, neuroma excision, nail surgery, etc.</p>

            <h2>Orthotics</h2>
            <p>Biomechanical instability is commonly the basis for foot pain or a painful deformity and functional custom orthotics are often prescribed.</p>

            <h2>Treatment of:</h2>
            <p>Plantar fasciitis/heel pain, arch pain, joint pain, bunions, hammertoes, neuromas, ingrown toenails/deformed nails, warts, skin lesions, diabetic feet, gout, arthritis, cold injuries, etc.</p>

